{
  "stem": "107.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He was took-- taken back to the crematoria, shot, and-- I mean, for psychotics, we had heard before that that was their solution for psychotics, even psychotic Germans.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[HEBREW], which is Hebrew, means the hope, and became later the national anthem of Israel.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I was saying after six months that whole group of people, me included, were in this quarantine barracks waiting for the train.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was supposed to take us to the new camp, and it didn't come, and it didn't come, and we got in formation.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There's no train on the ramp.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We got underground information it's very bad.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Be prepared.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we knew that--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "By then, we really had heard that we would go to the gas chambers.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Our six months of-- of what they're called, quarantine, waiting for the Red Cross, were over, and we would just be all totally executed, because by then we knew what was going on there.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I fall-- fell asleep on the second night.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Day and night we had already waited there when I heard somebody calling my name, and somebody called me out and a few other people all from the hospital where I work, and said you have to go back to the hospital.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I was saved.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The next day the whole 6,000-- 5,000-- it wasn't 5,000 anymore because some had died by then-- about 4,600 went into the gas chambers.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And while they were in the gas chambers, before the doors were closed, they are singing the [HEBREW] and the Czech national anthem.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the chief of the whole Auschwitz camp and Mengele were standing there and laughing, and then they closed the door.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That was described by people who were there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Well, mercy help us.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, by then I was back in the hospital.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
